<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>We all make recruiting mistakes tho, so (again a difference between us) I don't hold LC as a whole accountable for your attitude.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The only mistake LC could have made would have been if they'd tagged your two-faced ass, and they saw through you in time to avoid that. And I don't hold Wraith accountable for your attitude - I recognize that they'll act when you ask them to, though. Again, with emphasis: I still group with your guildmates. I wouldn't piss on you personally if you were on fire. And when I see a Wraith raid in a zone, I know any bad thing could happen because those otherwise pleasant people take their orders from people like you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I almost feel sorry for you, who plays a game not for fun but for malice. I do feel sorry for those that have to play with you. From both guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm sure you do. Just like I feel for the people that play in your guild and around you. Their reputations have been dragged through the mud by just about every guild you've come in contact with just through association, and they don't deserve it.<br>
<br>
And if you can point to one act of malice caused by me in game I'd be stunned.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I play for fun. I'm proud (at least in a video-game level) of my team and if we are 1st, 2nd, or 24th in server doesn't matter to me. My goals are to be the best my team can be, not be better than others.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Guess I hold myself to a higher standard. I want to be part of a guild that goes in and wins with class, which has fun and has standards. <br>
<br>
A guild that can be proud of learning the game itself, and not relying on ex-guildmates on Antonius Bayle to feed us strategies. We found out about the PoV flag by sending people through the trials. We recently figured out all the trials by sending people through them until we won. We're scouting out flag mobs by sending people to fight them, not sending people to The Safehouse to print out stuff. Like the gnome says: if we ain't dyin', we ain't tryin'!<br>
<br>
Unlike a lot of the other guilds on other servers, we actually treat other guilds with respect. You aren't going to find another Emperor-capable guild extending a rotation to guilds that haven't beaten him before. That actually leaves an area (like the Fear episode) when we find out a deal was already in place, or that we've been beaten in force. We're not the 400 pound gorilla that we could be, and it's a source of pride.<br>
<br>
We've created an atmosphere which is as casual-friendly as can be. We've always lagged behind other guilds, like Vis or Wraith, in setting standards for recruits. The only reason we put in the recent Vex Thal shard requirement was so we could actually see recruits in a raid environment! We have many players with playtimes that would get them /guildremoved in an instant by top guilds on other servers. Look at the thread on being &quot;left behind&quot; on FoH's site for an example of that.<br>
<br>
Delores Mulva<br>
Lotus Cult<br>
