Salta,<br>
<br>
Are you serious?<br>
<br>
Let me clue you in on a tiny insignificant thing called common sense.<br>
<br>
If one is not in a rotation, one cannot break it.    Rel and Explicit are not &quot;breaking the rotation&quot; on cursed when they try, are they?  NO!  Why?  THEY AREN&quot;T IN IT!   Duh.<br>
<br>
You may think it's fair to tell someone they can never try new content.  We don't.  I totally understand Rel and Explicit gunning for Cursed (or in the future possibly Emp)  even on &quot;my&quot; turn because they have no option but to compete FFA, or not do it, or negotiate.  If Soullance or Sephrok approached us to negotiate, we'd negotiate.  We'd tell them the current deal, and if Vis/LC agreed to let them in, we'd be all for it ... and if they decided it wasn't for them, that's fine.   If they decided the deal wasn't for them yet still wanted to try the mobs, while there might be conflict, we would not demonize them for going ffa.  We were ok with Rel joining cursed rotation four months ago, when we had just started him, before Explicit was even around.  <br>
<br>
<br>
What is it with the guilds that think they kill a mob first they own it for the rest of time?  Nobody needs your (or Wraith's) permission, nor are required to agree to your (or our) terms  to try new mobs.  <br>
<br>
When did we bitch on the boards about LC monopolizing?  <br>
<br>
We kill what we want.  We have no interest in bothering anyone else doing so.  We understand we aren't alone on the server and conflict is going to happen sometimes.  We handle it the best we can, without trying to force our terms on others.  Sometimes we back down, or the other guy backs down.  Sometimes neither does and we end up in a spat.  We try to reslove those becoming repeated with negotiation.   We understand negotiation is not &quot;my way or the highway&quot;.  <br>
<br>
<br>
We have no issues with LC as a whole.. We have had incidents with them that we disagreed on, and LC has done a few things that we felt were not very nice, but that's the game, we compete.  It's no big deal.  The most important thing is, for now at least LC still has sensible people at the helm who are willing to talk things over and be civil.  <br>
<br>
<br>
You guys (individuals not the guild) carry the chips on your shoulders... we've done nothing that your team hasn't  done, or that every fulltime raiding guild hasn't done.   The only reason we have your ire is we have the option (ie the skill and numbers)  to actually negotiate with you rather than do whatever you tell us to. <p>Gurunt Bangoo &lt;Wraith&gt;<br>
